Kiryukan Dojo, Cubao<br><br></span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><br>All
are cordially invited to the 116th FFA monthly interclub practice.
Interclubs enrich us by allowing us to glimpse the unaccustomed
emphases and unique subtleties of different Aikido sub-communities.
They help us avoid an ingrown and self-referential approach to studying
Aikido, or anything else. This series of joint monthly practice
sessions started in September 2000. The FFA is home to some of the
oldest, most experienced Aikido dojos in the Philippines. The FFA is
recognized by Japan Aikikai.</span><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Details:</span><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">THIS MONTH'S HOST:</span><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Kiryukan
 Dojo</span><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">THIS MONTH'S VENUE:</span><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Kiryukan Dojo</span><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">126 10th Ave., 
Cubao, QC**</span><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">DATE AND TIME:</span><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Saturday, 2011 January 08</span><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">1830 
hrs (6:30 p.m.)</span><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">(For easier recall, interclub practice always starts 
at 6:30 p.m. regardless of venue.)</span><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"></span></font></span></small><font style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);" size="2"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">PRACTITIONERS
FROM NON-AFFILIATED DOJOS VERY WELCOME. For more details, e-mail
<span style="border-bottom: 2px dotted rgb(54, 99, 136); background: transparent none repeat scroll 0% 50%; -moz-background-clip: initial; -moz-background-origin: initial; -moz-background-inline-policy: initial; cursor: pointer;" class="yiv322818728yiv1608554077yiv898408284yshortcuts" id="yiv322818728yiv1608554077yiv898408284lw_1283069715_1">macaikido@yahoo.com</span> or call 890-1976 (Marlene or Barbi).</span><strong style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"> <br><br>Mat fee: PhP100.</strong><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">
  </font><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><small style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><font size="2"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">-------------------------------</span><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">**
 Getting there:</span><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">a)
DRIVING YOUR CAR: Picture yourself on EDSA going north towards Cubao.
After crossing the EDSA/Santolan (now known as Boni Serrano)
intersection, keep to the right. Upon approaching the P.Tuazon
underpass, decline to go down the underpass; instead stay at ground
level and turn right (i.e. east) onto P.Tuazon.</span><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Drive along P.
Tuazon for approximately 700 meters. Find 10th Avenue and turn right
into it. No. 126 is the third property on the left. Park on the street.</span><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">b)
 DRIVING YOUR CAR (ver.2): This is perhaps a superior route for traffic avoidance:</span><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Picture
yourself
 on EDSA going north towards Cubao. Turn right (i.e. east) on
Santolan (now known as Boni Serrano Ave.). Turn left (i.e., north
again) on 10th Ave. Keep going until you see #126 on the right, just
three lots before you hit P.Tuazon.</span><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">c) COMMUTING (via MRT or LRT2
 train) Take train to Cubao. Get off at the Cubao station.</span><br style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Upon exiting MRT or LRT2 Cubao train station, walk in an approximately easterly/south-easterly direction
(towards the Araneta Coliseum/SM Cubao). Make your way to ShoeMart (SM)
Cubao, which is on P.Tuazon. It happens that 10th Ave. intersects
P.Tuazon near ShoeMart Cubao and Ali Mall. The dojo, at #126 10th Ave.,
is just three lots from the corner of 10th Ave and P.Tuazon.</span></font></span></small><font size="2"><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">
</font> 
